items.text: Awesome coffee, nice place to chill
Has a section with comfortable couches and low tables perfect for screwing around on your laptop or (gasp) actually reading a book.
seafood pasta is awesome!
Under renovation. Dec 22, 2013
Cozy, quite small though. Wi fi, lots of books and magazines and some children playing around. Bring your laptop, get a latte and feel like you are at the communal kitchen struggling with your essay.
Free wifi = perfect for remote working outside in the morning when it's not too hot
8 dollar tea pot is pricy, but i guess if you sit here for a while working it's sort of fair.
Busy but quiet place to relax and enjoy a coffee.
Breakfast was overrated. Hardly the write up in the epicure magazine. Disappointed.
Iced lime green tea!
This place is an oasis of calm  ... highly recommended for a good chill session
Fast wifi, great food and good atmosphere. Wouldn't come back for the coffee though...
See this cafe across from Illy cafe from Studio M
You can spend an entire afternoon with friends here - coffee and food is good. For tourists, they offer free WiFi here.
Grab the cosy two seater at the corner, good lighting for reading. The cheesecake and hot honey lemon are perfect for a rainy day.
Definitely came here for the atmosphere.The coffee was all right but it's a great place to study or get work done.They have a wonderful reading selection and the staff members are very friendly.
A glass of Chardonnay ...
Nice and cosy place to spend the lazy Sunday afternoon.
excellent banana milkshake!
Delicious smoked salmon benny and coffee.
Yummy apple pie here! And one of the cosiest place to read a book:)
Books. Coffee. Wifi. Powerpoints. Couches. Outside smoking area. All day breakfast. This place is a recipe for win. What's not to like, honestly?
Filling breakfast: We come here for 3 things: omelette, their big plate of sausages, eggs, bacon & hashbrown; & eggs Benedict. We always leave contented
Super chilled place. Some cool magazines to read e.g. T3.
The portions are small and not that delicious. The prices are high. It's an okay cafe, but overhyped.
Super comfortable place to work at!
great ambience for bookworms & some me-time
Cute location and has wifi, but the food and drinks are not amazing. The soy latte is my go-to drink here.
Great breakfast, books and coffee& coach. 👏👏👏
Charming little cafe perfect for lazing with a novel in hand.
best place to work so far in SG - free wifi, many outlets, comfy sofas, friendly service, excellent coffee, decent food :)
Be prepare to wait longer during lunch time, must have time to relax and eat here
Free wifi but very crowded
Lovely prosciutto all day breakfast
Coffee is ok. Breakfast of eggs Benedict was pretty terrible and made me ill. Also, skimped on the hollandaise sauce. Service was slow & terrible.
Had a nice cheese and mushroom omelette ...
Finally a place with Wi Fi in Singapore. And a lovely atmosphere to go with
Great service, always going around topping up our water. And plenty of power sockets outdoors for those who fancy doing work while smoking... with free WiFi!
A great cafe to chill out, peaceful and comfy. Food is good too, they have all my favorites. I love their yolkless cheesecake!
Terrible avocado chicken sandwich. Bread wasn't toasted and I was expecting a bigger potion for that price.
The latte here is nice and creamy.
Good range of local magazines, but was hoping to see more updated regional publications..
Awesome place to read a book alone !
Everything. Coffee, food, place seating area, location.
Awesome place!
Asked for a piccolo but nay, no can do. So went for a flat white instead. To my surprise, a small cup of delicious warm cuppa came. U've got urself a returning customer fo' shizzle.
Had the cheese burger and it's very good. Mildly crispy buns and beef patty's done just right with the right mix and doneness.
Great place for coffee and working. Lots of plug sockets. Cosy area to break out and read. Nice cakes too.
Great service staff. I just stopped by The Book Cafe yesterday for a drink to cool down the heat in Singapore. Longan Frosty killed.
Great lattes and food, good people watching as well.  Check their schedule as particular nights have group gatherings that fill the place.
Worked at the Book Cafe. Good wifi. hope they use Cisco / Linksys routers
Love the lemongrass & giber tea here.
Having a nice cup of cappuccino here. It's pleasant to read a book while sitting in the huge comfy sofa :)
AA8665A1D2
Please try the bratwurst. Please. It's crazy amazing!!!!!!!!
Yogurt is amazing. Nice place for a chat
Ask questions- for example: the breakfast set strictly ends after 11:30 AM BUT you can ask for the all day breakfast. They won't suggest it otherwise. :p
Terrible experience. $8 for a tea bag and the water was cold.  Eventually got some hot water, but they would not give me a new tea bag. Then they delivered my meal to the wrong table. Avoid.
Decent omelet and iced latte. It was a nice quiet spot for calls and work!
Favourite hangout spot
Chicken avocado with waku(?) dressing is so yummi
Best French Toast in Singapore !!
Nice chill out cafe to sit and read books. It has a great manga collection

Service is a bit chaotic but the coffee is great and the whole place has a great atmosphere. Don't order fresh juice, it comes in a small glass and not the best either. Food is fine, good brunch place
Love their Latte. Tastes good. Many power plugs available. Comfortable environment.
Very chill to work (everyone does), you can either work inside, on the lazy couches, surrounded by books or at the tables or on the terrace. Good all day breakfast and very good coffees. Free Wi-Fi.
Well..it is a kind of living room feeling so kind of a place to relax...that's fine..only..why in empty cafe getting the order takes 30min...nobody knows
The cafe was not as quiet as I hoped due to some rowdy girls. But it was still nice to sit here for a few hours. The food & coffee is above average but not amazing.
I do find it incredibly value for money. It invites you to sit as long as you like, browsing their range of reading materials.
Cozy and quiet place for reading books. The apple pie was delicious!!
The turkey ham Avocado egg white sandwich is excellent!! Coffee kinda weak for me..  #ThomtoriEats
Coffee and food (I had the salmon breakfast) could be better but great service, lovely ambience and very well air conditioned.
Usual morning coffee at this familiar haunt.
For the lactose intolerant, one of the few places in Singapore where soy milk is an easy option for coffee and even milkshakes!
Lots of power sockets and comfy sofas. Dim lighting. Somewhat annoying and inconsistent music. And lots of books and magazines to browse. Heard the food's so-so but smells good from where I was.
delightfully warm & attentive service -- serve 'em a Nobel Prize already 
On a less than crowded evening. Feeling so relaxed sitting on my own sofa and not having to feel cramped.
The dinner set comes with choice of full serving of soup of yr choice, mains plus dessert of the day with drinks. Quite a good deal
Super friendly staff actually encourage you to set up camp with your laptop by showing you the power points! Great place to work or chill as long as you want. And the lemon pinenut pie is awesome!

One of my favorite places when I travel to singapore. The staff is friendly and competent. The food is suprisingly good. There are plugs everywhere, one can spend whole afternoon catching up on emails
Choose the Wifi network with the face. Wifi password is 12345678.
Fries and molten choc cake. Just right.
Very disappointing! No coffee, no banana, no pancake @10am... and the waitress waited for 20mn to tell us. What sort of cafe serves no coffee or decent Bfast???
One of the places to be 'lost in time' for bookworms and coffee lovers in Singapore! I love the coffee, lovely service, sofas, books and the cakes - in that order! Price is okay for a frequenter.
Food is mediocre at best and overpriced. You are really paying for the environment, it's relaxed and can chill here all day without the staff pressuring you to order more food or asking you to leave
All time favourite cafe with smoking area and good service / free wifi
Was told i couldn't change table on a weekend. Strange policy. Was assigned table facing the wall. Food was good, service was weird .
Be aware it's crowded Sunday afternoon, and there is a smoking area if you don't want to sit in accidentally. The flat white is good.

This is a very hip and trendy cafe on River Valley Close area. I found the service good as well as the food. A great selection of food and drinks on offer with reasonable prices. Below's salmon ceasar
lovely to sit outside especially if its cooling at night.
longan freeze is refreshing ! not fan of their banana+orange smoothie. wireless surf spot with lotsa powerpoints :)
The drinks were okay only. Ice chocolate was quite tasteless. But the ambience for chilling out was good. Comfy sofa seats! The Oreo cheesecake is nice!
Weekend special lemon pine nut pie is yum. As others commented the staff is super friendly and makes you feel comfortable working here for hours. Wifi + sofa + good food make a productive afternoon~
Always attentive service and often good coffee. Average food though.
Great place to chill out! Seafood pasta is awesome!
free wifi and very nice atmosphere. only drank the tea, so can't comment on food.
Great coffee and dessert, while you can browse their extensive library of new magazines, travel guides and books.
Seafood pasta is very weak and watery but generous with garlic and veggie bits. Coffee is good.
They use real honey instead of the commercial sugar syrup, awesomely refreshing to order an iced honey lemon on a hot day and hazelnut chocolate cake is delicious but not overly sweet
Coffee. Cosy. Chill out afternoon
Liked the eggs Royale a lot!
Don't like the olive rice. Too oily for my taste. It is like library in a cafe. Try the steakhouse fries. Nice
Curry Chicken is THE BOMB!!!
Tried the Eggs Benedict and pan fried cod fish dinner set.  One of the poached eggs is a little bit overdone. Cosy place for you to chill over some magazines and books. GREAT SERVICE too!! =)
Great coffee and French toast
If you love the combination of a good book with a fresh pot of tea like me, don't forget to try Thai Lemongrass & Ginger tea. Sheer pleasure for your body & soul.
A great place to start my day. The latte is smooth, real smooth. Great breakfast!
Everyone loves to chill out here with something to read.
Comfy little place for wasting away the afternoon with great coffee and a good book
Cozy. Free wifi. Long black $4.5.
Celeb spotting: just saw our pal Woody grab a coffee here. If you see him say "Hi Allen". He prefers to stay anonymous
Great coffee, lovely staff, and a nice relaxed atmosphere with mellow music. Perfect for Monday morning breakfast before a hectic day, and free Wi-Fi too.
Had a glass of Cabernet Sauvignon, a coffee and a piece of lemon pie. Good service. Familiar staff. Nice atmosphere.
Hearty breakfast served all day.. Tex Mex chilli with corn chips are brilliant with a book and cuppa... Love the sofas.
Great place to hang out, there's a good selection of reading material and comfy couches. Plus free wifi and plenty of power points. Staff will even provide extension cords.
Really good tall black coffee here. You don't get that too often here in Singapore.
Their New York cheesecake is second to none and the manager Alan is excellent
The traditional baked lemon and & pine nut pie is good!
Nice, quiet place with a relaxing corner with sofa and lots of books (duh) and magazines to browse from.
Coffee good,  breakfast mediocre, environment a plus
Love the coffee and ambience!
